node.text:
To celebrate international yoga day, we invited our IIN ambassador @withyohanna to hold an online yoga class for you. 🧘‍♀️ 

Yohanna is a yoga teacher and wellness coach based in Stockholm, Sweden. After healing from burnout and eating disorder, she now guides ambitious women to balanced and meaningful lives through coaching, events and retreats. 🙏🏻

Yohanna happily shares her experience of being a student of IIN and welcome you to reach out via IG to ask questions. Remember to mention “Yohanna Mannelqvist” when you book your program to receive her ambassador discount of $2000! 💕🙌🏼

node.text:
We got kicked out at the end of our yin yoga stretch, but had a great conversation about the importance of breathwork & stretching to overall mental & physical wellness. 

We also discussed my experience with IIN, what led me to the program & how it’s shaped my life, health & career. 

You can follow me @coachcalie to continue the discussion. And don’t miss out on the opportunity yet the IIN sample class linked in my Instagram profile.

node.text:
Get some fresh air and take these Trail Mix Cookies from @gatherednutrition out in the open air. Tell us what you think!

gluten free, dairy free, + nut free trail mix cookies (makes 20 cookies): 

1 cup sunflower butter
1 cup unsweetened finely shredded coconut flakes
1/2 cup dairy free chocolate chips
1/2 cup coconut sugar
1/2 cup unsweetened dried cranberries
1/2 cup dates, pits removed and chopped (about 4–5 dates)
1/4 cup sunflower seeds
2 large eggs
1 tsp vanilla extract
1/2 tsp baking soda
1/4 tsp sea salt

1. Preheat oven to 350°F and line a large baking sheet with parchment paper.
2. In a large bowl, add all of the ingredients and mix until everything is well combined.
3. Scoop out the dough into generous tablespoon-sized portions, leaving a little room between each cookie. Use your hands to shape the dough and slightly flatten the dough (but not too much).
4. Bake for 10-12 minutes, until cookies are set. Note: sometimes sunflower butter turns green when baked- if this happens don’t worry! It’s natural and nothing to be worried about!

node.text:
“IT’S HEEEERE! 🎓

This past year of learning with @nutritionschool has been nothing short of incredible!

📚I spent SO many hours right here, sitting in my dining room / office studying my face off.
Originally I started this journey to gain more clarity around my own health and well-being but I am walking away with so much more!

👩‍🎓 I’ve gotten to learn from some of the leading professionals in the health and wellness industry, so many experts I look up to!
(@drmarkhyman @drweil @robinberzinmd @drlibby @mastnkipp, Christiane Northrup, to name just a few)

⚖️I was able to develop a deeper understanding of how impactful the mind-body connection really is and that achieving balance has never been more important.

🥦 Nutrition can be overwhelming but it’s so important as food can be used as one of the most powerful tools in medicine!

✨And Health goes so much further than what’s on our plate:
It’s not a one size fits all issue - it’s about joy, belly laughs, it’s about how we manage our career, relationships, our mindset and doing the inner work. It’s about having the ability to step into your full potential and creating the energy and motivation to live your most fulfilling life!

💛Coming to this realization I knew I was meant to helping other people as well.
I feel so grateful to be a graduate of IIN and to be able to switch gears, follow my passion and make such an impact in people’s lives.

✨This last year grounded me and really made me focus on the things that truly matter!

🌟Thank you for all the support, learning and growing with me - this is just the beginning!”
 -Integrative Nutrition Health Coach @sieben_stein_   #iinhealthcoach #iinalumni #iingrad #healthcoach #iin

Monday morning refresh with a Cucumber Cooler from @rrayyme :
Ingredients
- 1 cucumber chopped
- 1 kiwi (peeled and chopped)
- 1-inch knob of fresh ginger
- 2 cups coconut water
- 1 tsp. honey (optional)
- 1 Tbsp. chopped cilantro
- handful of ice

Use a juicer or high powered blender to blend until smooth! Optional to add a handful of spinach!

This makes about 3 cups and will last in your fridge for two days.

node.text:
Pups and abs to inspire your Friday workout. Did you know pets can have a positive impact on your well-being. We love to see you having fun with your fitness routine. Workout courtesy of @nicolemrauch 

30 seconds on, 10 seconds off [i use IntervalTimer to track]

- side dips - really engage your core here and use those obliques to pull yourself up!

- lateral plank

- crossbody crunch - switch sides halfway through

- straight arm sit up

REPEAT 3x total.  #fridaymotivation

node.text:
Wise words this Wednesday from IIN Health Coach in training @by.mandee: "well-being is something that goes far beyond the food we put into our plates and nourish our bodies with. in order to truly master the practice of self care, it’s important that we take time out to get in touch with who we are on a deeper level. 

journal. meditate. read. create— find what feeds your soul + truly aligns your with your higher self. make time in your daily routine to nurture yourself and do what you need to feel whole. try new things, take a personality test, take chances, meet new people + disconnect from relationships that no longer serve you. remember, self love isn’t selfish🤍🙏🏼" #wellnesswednesday

node.text:
Banana Vanilla Nicecream Milkshake by @bewellandbalanced. Tastes like ice cream without the added sugar, chemicals and preservatives. Enjoy!

You Need: (serves 2)
-2 cups of frozen cauliflower 
-2 frozen bananas 
-2 servings of vanilla protein powder
-2 teaspoons of Maca powder 
-2 (or more) scoops of coconut milk powder 
-1 tablespoon of hemp or chia seeds
-1/2 cup of vanilla creamer
-1 cup of unsweetened vanilla almond milk 
-1 scoop of ice
-1/2 cup of cold water 

Blend & enjoy
#nutritionschool
